==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*wurþa-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[wurd]], Old High German [[wurt]], Old Norse [[urðr]] (Swedish [[öde]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /wyrd/

===Noun===
'''wyrd''' ''f'' (''acc'' '''wyrd''' or '''wyrde''')
# [[fate]], [[destiny]]
# ''(in plural)'' the [[Fates]]
# an [[event]] or [[occurrence]]

===Descendants===
*English [[weird]]

